instructions:----------
This method takes an ArrayList of Strings as a parameter and returns
the longest String in the list. If the list is empty, it should return an
empty String. If there are more than one Strings with the max length, it should
return the first one with the longest length. For example, if an ArrayList
variable called list stores: {"once", "upon", "a", "time"}, the method should
return “once”
----------

